{"title_page": "Malin Burnham", "text_new": "{{short description|American sailor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Malin Burnham<!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|1927|11|12}}<!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year with {{Birth year and age|YYYY}} unless the exact date is already widely published, as per [[WP:DOB]]. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. -->\n| birth_place   = San Diego, California\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = \n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = \n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Malin Burnham''' (born November 12, 1927 in [[San Diego]], [[California]]<ref name=\"sdyc\">{{cite web |title=PH1412 People |url=http://sdyc.org/vewebsite/exhibit2/e21406a.htm |website=sdyc.org |publisher=San Diego Yacht Club |accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref>) is an American sailor who, at the age of 17, won the [[Star World Championships]] in 1944 (crewing for [[Gerald Driscoll]]) and 1945 (together with [[Lowell North]]). He was involved in [[Dennis Conner]]'s 1987 and 1988 [[Stars & Stripes (yacht)|Stars & Stripes]] [[America's Cup]] campaigns and named to the America's Cup Hall of Fame in 2002.<ref name=\"hall\">{{cite web |title=Herreshoff Marine Museum & America's Cup Hall of Fame |url=http://www.herreshoff.org/achof/malin_burnham.html |website=www.herreshoff.org |accessdate=16 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171219163538/http://www.herreshoff.org/achof/malin_burnham.html |archive-date=19 December 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"sdu\">{{cite web |title=Biography - Malin Burnham, Emeritus - School of Business - University of San Diego |url=https://www.sandiego.edu/business/centers-and-institutes/burnham-moores-real-estate/leadership/policy-advisory-board/biography.php?profile_id=7540 |website=www.sandiego.edu |accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref> Burnham was inducted into the [[National Sailing Hall of Fame]] in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nshof.org/inductees/burnham-malin/|title=Malin Burnham 2016 Inductee |publisher=Nshof.org |date= |accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref> He has a bachelor's degree in industriineering from [[Stanal engford University]].<ref name=\"sdu\"/>\n\nBurnham has been an active real estate developer in the San Diego area since the 1940s; his family real estate brokerage firm, Burnham Real Estate Services, was founded in 1891 and was acquired by [[Cushman & Wakefield]] in 2008.<ref>Mike Freeman, [http://www.utsandiego.com/uniontrib/20071218/news_1b18burnham.html \"N.Y. firm is buying Burnham brokers\"], ''[[U-T San Diego]]'', December 18, 2007.</ref> He is also known for his extensive charitable activities in San Diego.  The [[Sanford Burnham Prebys Medical Discovery Institute]] is partially named in his honor for his gift in 1996.\n\nBeginning in 2014 he led a group of San Diegans seeking to acquire the ''[[U-T San Diego]]'' newspaper from [[Doug Manchester]] and run it as a nonprofit entity.<ref>Fred Dickey, [http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2014/oct/13/malin-burnham-philantropist-newspaper-nonprofit/ \"Philanthropist's vision for buying U-T: Malin Burnham has big plan, 4 partners in bid for San Diego's largest news source.\"] ''[[U-T San Diego]]'', October 13, 2014.</ref><ref>Frank Gormlie, [http://sandiegofreepress.org/2014/10/what-does-malin-burnhams-possible-take-over-of-the-u-t-san-diego-mean/ \"What Does Malin Burnham\u2019s Possible Take-Over of the U-T San Diego Mean?\"], ''[[San Diego Free Press]]'', October 23, 2014, and [http://sandiegofreepress.org/2014/10/malin-burnham-and-the-u-t-san-diego-idea-factory/ \"Malin Burnham and the U-T San Diego Idea Factory\"], ''[[San Diego Free Press]]'', October 23, 2014.</ref>\n\nHe is a board member to [[Katerva]], called by [http://www.katerva.net/about/meet-board Reuters] as the Nobel Prize for Sustainability.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=257299&privcapId=21791346 Malin Burnham] executive profile, [[Bloomberg Business]]\n{{Footer World Champions Star}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burnham, Malin}}\n[[Category:American male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Star class sailors]]\n[[Category:People from San Diego]]\n[[Category:Philanthropists from California]]\n[[Category:American real estate businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1927 births]]\n[[Category:1987 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:1988 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:1977 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:Star class world champions]]\n[[Category:World champions in sailing for the United States of America]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American sailor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Malin Burnham<!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name -->\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by the blind and visually impaired's speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|1927|11|12}}<!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year with {{Birth year and age|YYYY}} unless the exact date is already widely published, as per [[WP:DOB]]. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. -->\n| birth_place   = San Diego, California\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = \n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = \n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n'''Malin Burnham''' (born November 12, 1927 in [[San Diego]], [[California]]<ref name=\"sdyc\">{{cite web |title=PH1412 People |url=http://sdyc.org/vewebsite/exhibit2/e21406a.htm |website=sdyc.org |publisher=San Diego Yacht Club |accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref>) is an American sailor who, at the age of 17, won the [[Star World Championships]] in 1944 (crewing for [[Gerald Driscoll]]) and 1945 (together with [[Lowell North]]). He was involved in [[Dennis Conner]]'s 1987 and 1988 [[Stars & Stripes (yacht)|Stars & Stripes]] [[America's Cup]] campaigns and named to the America's Cup Hall of Fame in 2002.<ref name=\"hall\">{{cite web |title=Herreshoff Marine Museum & America's Cup Hall of Fame |url=http://www.herreshoff.org/achof/malin_burnham.html |website=www.herreshoff.org |accessdate=16 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171219163538/http://www.herreshoff.org/achof/malin_burnham.html |archive-date=19 December 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"sdu\">{{cite web |title=Biography - Malin Burnham, Emeritus - School of Business - University of San Diego |url=https://www.sandiego.edu/business/centers-and-institutes/burnham-moores-real-estate/leadership/policy-advisory-board/biography.php?profile_id=7540 |website=www.sandiego.edu |accessdate=16 March 2019}}</ref> Burnham was inducted into the [[National Sailing Hall of Fame]] in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nshof.org/hall-of-fame/196-the-national-sailing-hall-of-fame/hall-of-fame-2016/1022-burnham-malin-2016-hall-of-fame-lifetime-achievement-award|title=Malin Burnham 2016 Inductee |publisher=Nshof.org |date= |accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref> He has a bachelor's degree in industrial engineering from [[Stanford University]].<ref name=\"sdu\"/>\n\nBurnham has been an active real estate developer in the San Diego area since the 1940s; his family real estate brokerage firm, Burnham Real Estate Services, was founded in 1891 and was acquired by [[Cushman & Wakefield]] in 2008.<ref>Mike Freeman, [http://www.utsandiego.com/uniontrib/20071218/news_1b18burnham.html \"N.Y. firm is buying Burnham brokers\"], ''[[U-T San Diego]]'', December 18, 2007.</ref> He is also known for his extensive charitable activities in San Diego.  The [[Sanford Burnham Prebys Medical Discovery Institute]] is partially named in his honor for his gift in 1996.\n\nBeginning in 2014 he led a group of San Diegans seeking to acquire the ''[[U-T San Diego]]'' newspaper from [[Doug Manchester]] and run it as a nonprofit entity.<ref>Fred Dickey, [http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2014/oct/13/malin-burnham-philantropist-newspaper-nonprofit/ \"Philanthropist's vision for buying U-T: Malin Burnham has big plan, 4 partners in bid for San Diego's largest news source.\"] ''[[U-T San Diego]]'', October 13, 2014.</ref><ref>Frank Gormlie, [http://sandiegofreepress.org/2014/10/what-does-malin-burnhams-possible-take-over-of-the-u-t-san-diego-mean/ \"What Does Malin Burnham\u2019s Possible Take-Over of the U-T San Diego Mean?\"], ''[[San Diego Free Press]]'', October 23, 2014, and [http://sandiegofreepress.org/2014/10/malin-burnham-and-the-u-t-san-diego-idea-factory/ \"Malin Burnham and the U-T San Diego Idea Factory\"], ''[[San Diego Free Press]]'', October 23, 2014.</ref>\n\nHe is a board member to [[Katerva]], called by [http://www.katerva.net/about/meet-board Reuters] as the Nobel Prize for Sustainability.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=257299&privcapId=21791346 Malin Burnham] executive profile, [[Bloomberg Business]]\n{{Footer World Champions Star}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burnham, Malin}}\n[[Category:American male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Star class sailors]]\n[[Category:People from San Diego]]\n[[Category:Philanthropists from California]]\n[[Category:American real estate businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1927 births]]\n[[Category:1987 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:1988 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:1977 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:Star class world champions]]\n[[Category:World champions in sailing for the United States of America]]\n", "name_user": "Cajohnson56", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixed NSHOF reference link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malin_Burnham"}
